<section id="about" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lAbout">About Tamil Nadu</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="aboutTitle">The Cradle of <em>Dravidian Civilization</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="aboutBody">Tamil Nadu, the jewel of South India, is the birthplace of Dravidian civilization with unbroken traditions spanning over 2000 years. Home to magnificent temples with intricate Chola dynasty architecture, classical arts that captivate millions, and the world's oldest living literary tradition, Tamil Nadu stands as a beacon of cultural excellence. From the Brihadeeshvara Temple in Thanjavur to the serene backwaters and hill stations, from the bustling metropolis of Chennai to the spiritual shores of Kanyakumari where three seas meet, Tamil Nadu embodies the perfect harmony of ancient wisdom and modern progress. A land of saints and scholars, artists and entrepreneurs, Tamil Nadu continues to preserve its unparalleled heritage while embracing the future with confidence and grace.</p>
</section>

<section id="weather" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lWeather">Climate &amp; Best Time</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="weatherTitle">When to Visit <em>Tamil Nadu</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="weatherNote" style="margin-bottom:0">Tamil Nadu experiences distinct seasons with hot summers (March-May), southwest monsoon (May-August), northeast monsoon (October-December), and cool pleasant winters. October to January is ideal for most destinations across the state.</p>
